## Third-Party Software and Licenses

Angry-BOX acts as an orchestrator and depends on several critical third-party open-source projects. By using Angry-BOX, you also agree to the licensing terms of these underlying components.

### 1. sing-box and sing-box-extended
Angry-BOX automatically downloads and installs `sing-box-extended`, a community fork of `sing-box`.
* **Repository:** [SagerNet/sing-box](https://github.com/SagerNet/sing-box) / [shtorm-7/sing-box-extended](https://github.com/shtorm-7/sing-box-extended)
* **License:** GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPLv3)
* **Copyright:** SagerNet and contributors.

### 2. AmneziaWG Linux Kernel Module
For WireGuard/AmneziaWG support, Angry-BOX builds and installs the `amneziawg-linux-kernel-module`.
* **Repository:** [amnezia-vpn/amneziawg-linux-kernel-module](https://github.com/amnezia-vpn/amneziawg-linux-kernel-module)
* **License:** GNU General Public License v2.0 (GPLv2)
* **Copyright:** Amnezia VPN and original WireGuard authors (Jason A. Donenfeld).

### 3. HTMX and TailwindCSS / DaisyUI (Web UI)
* **HTMX:** [BSD 2-Clause License](https://github.com/bigskysoftware/htmx/blob/master/LICENSE)
* **TailwindCSS:** [MIT License](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/blob/master/LICENSE)
* **DaisyUI:** [MIT License](https://github.com/saadeghi/daisyui/blob/master/LICENSE)

*All trademarks, logos and brand names are the property of their respective owners. All company, product and service names used in this project are for identification purposes only.*
